OL,7,FA Year 6 Sats paper that left some
OL,8,Fchildren in tears has been published
OL,9,Fearly, after complaints the test was
OL,10,Ftoo difficult.
OL,12,FThe key stage two exam was sat by 10-
OL,13,F and 11-year-olds last week. They
OL,14,Fwere required to answer 38 questions
OL,15,Fbased around three set texts.
OL,17,FOne of these texts, about a large bat
OL,18,Fcolony, was adapted from a New York
OL,19,FTimes article, while another came
OL,20,Ffrom The Rise of Wolves, which has a
OL,21,Freading age of 13 and over.
OL,3,CHow would you fare on the Sats
OL,4,Creading paper that left Year 6 pupils
OL,5,Cin tears?
